# OneThing Directory Contract

OneThing is the canonical replacement for Todos. It is Afenda's operational focus surface for resolving business consequences.

## Prime directive

> **OneThing optimizes for operational inevitability, not feature discoverability.**

Every UI / IA / API decision in this directory is judged against that line. If a proposed addition makes the surface easier to *find* features but reduces the *inevitability* with which an operator resolves business reality, the proposal is rejected. Discoverability gains are not a defense.

Practical consequences of this directive (each enforced below):

- Whitespace, typography, and a single brand accent carry hierarchy. Status badges, severity pills, and counters carry it instead → rejected.
- Capture is implicit and structureless. Metadata strips at capture, "Add to project" pickers, and category dropdowns improve discoverability of organization features → rejected.
- The five-control toolbar is the cap. A sixth control is always discoverable; it is also always destructive to the doctrine → rejected.
- Tutorial chrome (help chips, coach marks, tooltips on shortcuts) increases discoverability and reduces the surface's claim to be operational memory → rejected.
- Animation theater (FLIP reconciliation, scale-in detail pane, pulse on save) makes capability legible at the cost of feeling consequential → rejected.

When in doubt: **subtract.**

## Category framing (the doctrine)

OneThing is **operational document computing**, not a productivity dashboard, not a ticket queue, not an AI sidekick. The product surface is a two-pane document reader for unresolved business reality.

Mature comparators (lean toward these): Notes, Mail, Things 3, Finder, Terminal.
Anti-comparators (do not lean toward these): Linear, Slack, Superhuman, Notion, Asana, Jira.

Rule out (forbidden):
- KPI tiles, dashboard cards, count badges in the list pane header.
- "AI assistant" surfaces inside OneThing (Lynx is a sidecar, not a panel inside OneThing).
- Workflow-builder energy: graph canvases, automation studios, branching node UIs.
- Tutorial chrome: keyboard help chips, coach marks, first-run overlays, onboarding tours.
- Status badges, severity pills, assignee avatar stacks, role chips, label tags on list rows.
- Two-line list rows; preview text under the title; section labels other than `Today`.
- Productivity-app cognitive load (filters, saved views, swimlanes, tabs).

Rule in (required):
- Single-line list rows: title carries the situation; ambient time + optional 6px activity dot.
- Editorial detail pane: large headline, narrative byline, prose body, inline `<sup>` predictions.
- Implicit save on capture: composer drafts persist in `localStorage`; clear only on Server Action success.
- Five-control toolbar maximum (resolve · snooze · comment · pin · more).
- Continuity audit footer reads as a thread, not a label grid.

## Required product model

- Lead with consequence, owner, evidence, time, and next safe action.
- UI language is Past · Now · Next.
- Internal temporal model may use Past / Present / Future aliases, where Present maps to Now and Future maps to Next.
- Resolution is stronger than completion: resolve only when consequence, proof, audit, and downstream safety are handled.
- 7W1H audit renders as readable narrative first, with structured inspection secondary.
- CRUD-SAP is an internal grammar only. Do not expose it as ordinary user-facing copy.

## Required state language

- Use operational states: `detected`, `owned`, `blocked`, `resolving`, `ready_to_release`, `released`, `resolved`, `deprecated`.
- Use severity language: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `critical` (audit / ranker only — never as visible row chrome).

## Title-as-situation contract

The single-line list pane only works if the title carries the full operational situation. The contract is enforced at three layers:

1. **Schema (hard gate, new captures only)** — `createOrgOneThingSchema` uses `onethingSituationTitleSchema` (= `onethingTitleSchema.superRefine(assertOneThingTitleIsSituation)`). The refine rejects three structural shapes with `OneThingTitleNotSituation`:
   - `technical_event_tail` — trailing em-dash + technical event verb (`"Vendor payment — RG-FIN-014 failed"`).
   - `module_noun_prefix` — `"PO:"`, `"Contact:"`, etc.
   - `single_token` — bare one-word labels.
2. **Lynx ranker (soft advisory)** — non-situation titles surface a faint, dismissible inline rephrase prompt. Never blocks the work.
3. **Composer placeholder** — demonstrates the rule by example so the operator learns the shape implicitly.

The lenient `onethingTitleSchema` stays permissive for legacy data, imported rows, and update paths. Do not apply the strict refine on update or import.

## Row anatomy contract (list pane)

The single-line row anatomy is locked:

```
[focused-row rail (2px, primary, focused only)]
[title — font-semibold for critical/high, normal otherwise; opacity 60% when viewed and not focused]
[activity dot (5px, primary, only when updated within the last hour and not focused)]
[ambient time (11px, muted, no `font-variant-numeric`)]
```

Forbidden in list rows:
- Two-line layouts; preview text under the title.
- Severity badges, status pills, role chips, assignee avatars, counterparty labels.
- Tabular-nums on the time column (it implies dataset, not memory).
- Section labels other than `Today` (when items exist there).

Row min-height: 44px. Density should feel like Things 3 / Mail compact — not Linear / Asana.

## Detail-pane editorial typography

- Headline: `clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.4rem)` with `line-height: 1.08` and `letter-spacing: -0.04em` — document-level, not card-level.
- Body: 16px / `leading-[1.85]`, `max-width: 64ch`. Past · Now · Next render as paragraphs with no labels.
- Predictions render as inline `<sup>` markers within the Now paragraph, with a numbered footnote list below. No separate "Connected truth" panel with chrome.
- Why-now is a quiet italic caption, not a chunky pill.
- No labeled stakes block; the body's prose carries the weight.

## Toolbar contract

Maximum five controls in the detail-pane toolbar: `resolve · snooze · comment · pin · more`. The decision console is folded into the inline resolve expander; there is no separate console screen. `more` hides the long tail (reopen, delete, purge, deprecate). The `pin` slot is reserved (the rule contract owns the placement so the pinned-row rail in the list pane has a place to ship into).

## Composer contract

- Title-only field (consequence, severity, dueAt come from the detail pane after capture).
- Implicit save: `localStorage` key `afenda:onething:composer:<scope>:<listId>`, debounced, multi-tab synchronized via `storage` event, cleared only on Server Action success.
- `⌘ Enter` / `Ctrl+Enter` submits. `Esc` blurs.
- Multi-line paste is preserved (textarea auto-grows).
- Placeholder demonstrates the title-as-situation contract by example.

## Tutorial chrome

Production has no keyboard help chip, no toast tutor, no first-run coach mark. Discovery is through behavior. The composer placeholder is the only intentional teaching surface.

## Legacy behavior

- Old task-like complete/snooze/delete/import behavior may exist only as internal adapters under `lib/features/onething/data/legacy-*`.
- Do not export legacy task APIs from `#features/onething`.
- Do not model OneThing as generic workflow management. Workflow exists to support consequence resolution, not replace it.
- Do not let Workflow DevKit entrypoints (recurrence runs, reminder runs) become the product model. They are implementation details of consequence lifecycle, not product surface.

## Module imports

- Server composition and route wiring use `#features/onething` (`index.ts`).
- Client Components under `lib/features/onething/components/` import types, pure helpers, and **Server Actions** from `#features/onething/client` (not the server barrel). `OneThingShell` binds org vs personal actions from that barrel using `scope` + `canAdmin`.
- Server-only data layer queries / mutations re-export through `#features/onething/server`.
- After org/personal OneThing mutations or workflows, invalidate UI via `revalidateOrgOneThingDashboard` / `revalidatePersonalOneThingSurface` from `data/onething-revalidate.server.ts` (centralizes `revalidatePath` + locale patterns).

## Component file layout

```
lib/features/onething/components/
  onething-shell.tsx           — two-pane container, mobile slide-over, keyboard map
  onething-list-pane.tsx       — single-line ranked rows + composer
  onething-detail-pane.tsx     — editorial document (headline, byline, prose, predictions)
  onething-detail-toolbar.tsx  — five-control toolbar + folded resolve / deprecate / more
  onething-detail-composer.tsx — implicit-save composer (sits at top of list)
  onething-detail-empty.tsx    — quiet single-line empty state
  onething-detail-audit-footer.tsx — collapsible continuity thread
  onething-page.tsx            — RSC orchestrator (org)
  personal-onething-page.tsx   — RSC orchestrator (personal)
  hooks/
    use-focus-navigation.ts            — `?focus=` history-stack discipline
    use-resolve-with-focus-handoff.ts  — preserve momentum on resolve
    use-onething-draft-persistence.ts  — localStorage drafts
    use-flip.ts                        — ranker reconciliation FLIP
```

Do not add new top-level component categories without updating this rule first.
